    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with **Corbin Carroll** standing as the clear alpha, boasting a massive 80.85 efficiency score. While he faces the challenge of an elite catcher\u2019s pop time, his premium position at the two-hole and favorable park factors make him a locked-in start. **Josh Naylor** also highlights our core, providing a strong 69.07 output against a hittable 4.57 xERA, bolstered by a significant platoon advantage. We are also leaning heavily into the speed-to-stolen base correlation today: **Trevor Story** (67.13) and **Brice Turang** (66.23) are both surging in our projections due to favorable matchups against pitchers with slow deliveries, which directly addresses our league\u2019s scarcity in the SB category.\n\nTactical adjustments for this lineup are heavily dictated by platoon splits and environmental data. **Mickey Moniak** (65.00) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (58.38) are both seeing their projections inflated by dynamic platoon advantages, though **Mickey Moniak** carries a non-zero risk profile due to a 39% rain probability that warrants close monitoring. Conversely, **Dalton Rushing** is relegated to a bottom-tier start (40.61) due to the daunting task of facing deGrom; his lack of a platoon edge against a high-tier arm makes him a candidate for potential benching if we needed to preserve daily games, but he remains in the fold for now.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision landed on **Zach McKinstry**, who narrowly missed the starting cut with a 49.24 score. While he holds an advantage against the opponent\u2019s slow delivery, the combination of a low-leverage spot in the eighth slot and inferior base projections kept him behind the likes of **Tyler Soderstrom** and **Seiya Suzuki**. While **Max Muncy** (44.17) and **Jose Caballero** (40.23) were also analyzed, neither could overcome the efficiency threshold required to unseat our current starters. We are prioritizing the higher ceiling provided by **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (59.07) at the MI slot, betting on his ability to maximize the five-spot in the order despite a tougher matchup against Rasmussen.",
